sentences: Enrica Clay Dillon (June 22, 1885 – October 9, 1946) was an American opera singer, opera director, and voice teacher.
Born in 1885 in Denver, Colorado, Dillon was the daughter of Judge Henry Clay Dillon and Florence (née Hood) Dillon.
She was the older sister of composer Fanny Dillon and actress Josephine Dillon; the latter of whom was married to Clark Gable for 6 years.
She had a prolific career as a dramatic soprano in Europe during the first decade and a half of the 20th century, giving more than 1,800 opera performances.
